Theodore Solso Biography

Mr. Theodore M. Solso, Tim has been Chief Executive Officer of Cummins Inc. (formerly, Cummins Engine Company Inc.) since January 2000. Mr. Solso has been Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of the Columbus Ind., manufacturer of electrical power generation systems, engines and related ...
>>Read More 


Mr. Theodore M. Solso, Tim has been Chief Executive Officer of Cummins Inc. (formerly, Cummins Engine Company Inc.) since January 2000. Mr. Solso has been Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of the Columbus Ind., manufacturer of electrical power generation systems, engines and related technologies since the beginning of 2000. He served as the President of Cummins Inc. from 1995 to 2000, Chief Operating Officer from 1994 to 2000 and Executive Vice President of Operations from 1992 to 1994. He served as Vice President and General Manager of Engine Business after serving in various other executive positions in Cummins Inc. from 1988 to 1992. Mr. Solso served in various positions with Cummins Engine Company Inc., since 1971. He served at Cummins as Vice President and General Manager of Holset, Vice President of special engine markets and Vice President of Marketing from 1980 to 1988. Mr. Solso began his career with Cummins in 1971 as Assistant to the Vice President of Personnel until 1972 and served as an Employment Director from 1972 to 1974. He also served as Director of Development and Training from 1974 to 1977 and Executive Director of personnel from 1977 to 1980 for Cummins. Mr. Solso has been Chairman of Cummins Inc., since January 2000. He serves as Chairman of the United Way Campaign-Bartholomew County. He has been an Independent Director of Ball Corporation since January 2003. He has been a Director of Cummins Inc., since 1994. Mr. Solso has been a Director of Ashland Inc., since 1999. He serves as a Director of Cummins Foundation, the Central Indiana Corporate Partnership, American Transportation Research Institute. He serves as a Member of the Boards of Cummins Engine Foundation, Heritage Fund of Bartholomew County in Columbus, Indiana and Otter Creek Golf Course in Columbus, Indiana. Mr. Solso serves as a Trustee of DePauw University and Manufacturers Alliance. He served as Director of Irwin Financial Corporation from 1993 to December 31, 2006. He served as a Director of Cyprus Amax Minerals Co., since November 15, 1993. He served as a Director of Amoco Corporation. He served as a Director of BP plc. and Indiana Economic Development Corp. He is also a Member of the Indiana Academy, a Member of the Business Roundtable and the Business Council. Mr. Solso received a Bachelor of Arts in Psychology from Depauw University in 1969 and an Masters in Business Administration from Harvard University in 1971.
